Correct Ans: 202. R uses lexical scoping, it looks for a variable/function in the current environment, if it doesn't find it then it moves one level up. In the above example, there are three `f`s defined. `f(10)` uses the outermost #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:03112021220019]

`f`, `f(x)*2` uses the second `f` and `f()+1` uses the innermost `f`'s definition. We can see which one got executed when, by wrapping the execution statements with `print()`. [see_image_1] #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:03112021220019] https://t.co/dwr5Fxk837
